            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-2 text-center">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  1 BC 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
Approximate time of the birth of Simon, son of Jonah, in the Galilean town of Bethsaida.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-2">
                <div id="content" class="well text-center">
                  AD 25-27
                </div>
              </div>  
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Simon marries and has children. His family, along with his mother in-law, settles in Capernaum.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-2 text-center">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  AD 30
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  While Peter and Andrew are fishing at the Sea of Galilee, Jesus sees them and asks them to follow Him and "become fishers of men" <a 
href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/4.18-22?lang=eng" target="_blank">Matthew 4:18–22</a>; <a   href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/1.16-18?lang=eng" target="_blank">Mark 1:16–18</a>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter casts his net in the Sea of Galilee after being told by Jesus to do so. He tells Jesus that they have tried all night to do so and without success. When he did as he was told, they caught a great number of fish. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/5.4-7?lang=eng" targe ="_blank">Luke 5:4-7</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
            </div> 
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-2 text-center">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  AD 31-32
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter sees Jesus walking on water, Peter walks on water to Jesus, but loses faith and sinks. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/14.28-29?lang=eng" target = "_blank">Matthew 14:28-29</a>
                </div>
              </div>
