                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Jesus predicts that Simon Peter will deny Him three times before a rooster crows. Peter tell Jesus he will never deny Him. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/26.34?lang=eng" target="_blank"><br>Matthew 26:34-35</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/14.30-31?lang=eng" target="_blank">Mark 14:30-31</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/22.34?lang=eng"target="_blank">Luke 22:34</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/13.38?lang=eng" target="_blank"> John 13:38</a>
      </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter and the other apostles slept while Jesus was suffered for our sins in The Garden of Gethsemane. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/26.40?lang=eng" target = "_blank">Matthew 26:40-46</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/14?lang=eng" target = "_blank">Mark 14:37-42</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/22.45-46?lang=eng" target = "_blank">Luke 22:45-46</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Jesus' prophecy of is fulfilled when Peter denies Him three times and then a rooster crows. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/26.69-75?lang=eng" target="_blank">Matthew 26:69-75</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/14.66-72?lang=eng" target="_blank">Mark 14:66-72</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/22.32?lang=eng" target="_blank">Luke 22:55-60</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/14.16-27?" target="_blank">John 18:16-27</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter and the other apostles receive word from Mary Magdalene that the body of Jesus is no longer there in the tomb. Peter rushes to Jesus’s tomb to confirm the news. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/16.10-11?lang=eng" target="_blank">Mark 16:10-11</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/24.9-11?lang=eng" target="_blank">Luke 24:9-12</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/20?lang=eng" target="_blank">John 20</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Jesus appears in front of the eleven apostles. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/16.14?lang=eng"target="_blank">Mark 16:14</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/24.36-39?lang=eng" target="_blank">Luke 24:36-39</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/20.19?lang=eng" target="_blank">John 20:19</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter and the other apostles recieve the gift of the Holy Spirit from Jesus and promises they will enjoy it soon. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/24.49?lang=eng" target="_blank">Luke 24:49</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/20?lang=eng" target="_blank">John 20:21-23</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter and a large group of people gather at a mountain in Galilee to see Jesus. He commissions them to share his gospel with the world. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/28.16-20?lang=eng" target="_blank">Matthew 28:16-20</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-cor/15.6?lang=eng" target="_blank">1 Corinthians 15:6</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  While Peter and six others were fishing at the Sea of Galilee, Jesus appears and ask them if they have any fish. Peter makes a confession of love towards the risen Jesus three times after meeting him on the shores of Galilee. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/21.15-17?lang=eng" target="_blank">John 21:15-17</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
