              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  On Pentecost, now enjoying the power of the Holy Spirit, Peter gives a message to the saints in Jerusalem. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/2.14-36lang=eng&clang=tam" target="_blank">Acts 2:14-36</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter confronts a husband and wife regarding property they lied about the price of. Both die upon questioning. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/5?lang=eng" target="_blank">Acts 5:3-9</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter and John are sent to Samaria to give them the gift of the Holy Ghost. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/n t/acts/8.14-17?lang=eng" target="_blank">Acts 8:14</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Peter travels to different places to teach and to encourage other believers in Jesus Christ. He also visits Lydda. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/9.32?lang=eng" target="_blank">Acts 9:32</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  God uses Peter to bring a little girl back to life. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/9.40?lang=eng" target="_blank">Acts 9:40</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Jewish believers in Jerusalem argue with Peter for being in the company of non-Jews. <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/  nt/acts/11.1-3?lang=eng" target="_blank">Acts 11:1-3</a> 
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-10">
                <div id="content" class="well">
                  Paul confronts Peter’s behavior when he is in the presence of non-Jewish believers and Jewish believers. <a   href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/gal/2.11-14?lang=eng" target="_blank">Galatians 2:11</a>
